<TITLE> Hasina meets Sri Lanka envoy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 5 (bdnews24.com)Sri Lankan High Commissioner V Krishnamoorthy met with the prime minister Sheikh Hasina Sunday. The Lankan envoy called on Sheikh Hasina at her office at 10am and spent half an hour discussing bilateral issues, said the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad. Krishnamoorthy condoled the shocking deaths of military officers killed at the Bangladesh Rifles headquarters in February and commended the way the prime minister and her government handled the mutiny peacefully. Hasina enquired about the state of Sri Lankan education and said The Bangladesh government would take effective measures to stop primary level drop out and would introduce free education for all from primary to graduation level soon. Krishnamoorthy congratulated the prime minister on her party's landslide victory in the national polls. Abul Kalam Azad and the PMO secretary Molla Wahiduzzaman were present.
